verbs.description: counterbrace (third-person singular simple present counterbraces, present participle counterbracing, simple past and past participle counterbraced)

entries.meaning: (nautical, transitive) To brace in opposite directions.
examples: To counterbrace the yards is to brace the head yards one way and the after yards another.

entries.meaning: (engineering, transitive) To brace in such a way that opposite strains are resisted.
